==變化==
[[File:Manhattan_cocktail.jpg|thumb]]]]

傳統的觀念認為，曼哈頓要與美國黑麥威士忌進行調和。然而，往往不是這樣，曼哈頓現在更多是與伯本或加拿大威士忌所調和而成。曼哈頓是擁有相當大的變化和創新空間的飲品，往往是調酒師展現自己的創造力的最佳利器<ref name="sfg"/>。有些人會搖晃調酒杯，而不是攪拌冰塊的部分，目的是為了使得飲料上展現泡沫。Angostura的是經典的苦精，但橘苦精，Peychaud的苦精，也可以使用。也有沒有任何苦精的曼哈頓，這種酒我們稱之為Fanciulli雞尾酒<ref>{{cite news |title=Making Bitter Fernet-Branca Much Easier to Swallow |newspaper=[[华尔街日报|The Wall Street Journal]] |first=Eric |last=Felten |date=January 3, 2009 |url=http://online.wsj.com/article/SB123092858411149807.html |accessdate=2010-04-16 |archive-date=2010-04-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100421140738/http://online.wsj.com/article/SB123092858411149807.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

一些人會使用自製的苦精和糖漿，用相似味道的東西代替苦艾酒，用些當地或罕見的威士忌，也可以用其他外來成分<ref name="sfg"/>。[[檸檬皮|檸檬皮]]可以用作裝飾。一些從櫻桃或馬拉希諾利口酒來調配出額外的甜度和色彩。

最初，都認為苦精是任何雞尾酒的必要成分，以區分雞尾酒（cocktail）和{{le|斯林酒|Sling (drink)}}（sling）<ref>{{cite news |title=The Origin of Cocktails |first=Steve |last=Levin |url=http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06132/689498-294.stm |newspaper=Pittsburgh Post-Gazette |date=May 12, 2006 |accessdate=2010-04-16 |archive-date=2011-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110522032109/http://www.post-gazette.com/pg/06132/689498-294.stm |dead-url=no }}</ref>。隨著時間的推移，雞尾酒和斯林酒的這些定義已經變得模糊，因為斯林酒普及率已經下降許多（是偶用在某些飲料的名稱上等），而雞尾酒可以泛指任何類似馬提尼酒，或只是任何混合飲用任何飲料。



The following are other variations on the classic Manhattan:
* A '''{{tsl|en|Rob Roy cocktail||Rob Roy}}''' is made with [[蘇格蘭威士忌|Scotch whisky]].<ref name="sfg"/>
* A '''Dry Manhattan''' is made with dry [[威末酒|vermouth]] instead of sweet vermouth, usually also replacing the maraschino cherry with a {{tsl|en|Twist (cocktail garnish)||twist}} in keeping with the overall principle of reducing the cocktail's sweetness.  A Manhattan made with dry vermouth but retaining the cherry rather than twist is sometimes known as a "half-dry Manhattan," but this name risks confusion with the "Perfect Manhattan" (see below), whose quantity of vermouth consists of equal parts sweet vermouth and dry vermouth.<ref name="sfg"/>
* A '''Perfect Manhattan''' is made with equal parts sweet and [[威末酒|dry vermouth]].<ref name="sfg"/>
* A '''Brandy Manhattan''' is made with [[白兰地|Brandy]] instead of whiskey and is very popular in [[威斯康辛州|Wisconsin]] and [[明尼蘇達州|Minnesota]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://onmilwaukee.com/bars/articles/brandy.html |title=OnMilwaukee.com Bars & Clubs: Wisconsinites love affair with brandy<!-- Bot generated title --> |accessdate=2016-02-02 |archive-date=2016-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203085546/http://onmilwaukee.com/bars/articles/brandy.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* A '''Metropolitan''' is similar to a brandy Manhattan, but with a 3-to-1 ratio of [[白兰地|brandy]] to [[威末酒|vermouth]].<ref name="wsj">{{cite news |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |accessdate=2007-10-22 |url=http://online.wsj.com/public/article/SB118919826671120943.html |title=In a League of Their Own: The Ivy League, That Is |first=Eric |last=Felten |date=September 8, 2007 |archive-date=2007-10-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071015000301/http://online.wsj.com/public/article/SB118919826671120943.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* A '''Cuban Manhattan''' is a Perfect Manhattan with [[兰姆酒|dark rum]] as its principal ingredient.<ref name="cm">{{cite web|url=http://greatcocktails.co.uk/Manhattan.html|accessdate=2007-10-22|publisher=Great Cocktails|title=Manhattan|archive-date=2012-02-21|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/65ckSg500?url=http://greatcocktails.co.uk/Manhattan.html|dead-url=yes}}</ref>
*A '''Tijuana Manhattan''' is made with an [[龍舌蘭酒|Anejo Tequila]].<ref>Donohue, Peter (Feb 2011) Azul 17 Tequila Lounge</ref>
*The '''Fourth Regiment''' is a classic (ca. 1889) cocktail that uses a 1/1 ratio of [[威士忌|whiskey]] and [[威末酒|vermouth]], and uses three dashes of three different {{tsl|en|bitters||bitters}} - {{tsl|en|orange bitters||orange bitters}}, celery bitters, and {{tsl|en|Peychaud's Bitters||Peychaud's Bitters}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.smallscreennetwork.com/video/630/cocktail_spirit_fourth_regiment/ |title=How to make the Fourth Regiment Cocktail - The Cocktail Spirit with Robert Hess |access-date=2016-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130427095612/http://www.smallscreennetwork.com/video/630/cocktail_spirit_fourth_regiment/ |archive-date=2013-04-27 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

